<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Sentiment analysis</h1>\t\t\t<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
\t\t\t\t<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\t\t\t\t<div id="contentSub"></div>
\t\t\t\t<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>\t\t\t\t<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
\t\t\t\t<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</a>
\t\t\t\t<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><b>Opinion mining</b> (sometimes known as <b>sentiment analysis</b> or <b>emotion AI</b>) refers to the use of <a href="/wiki/Natural_language_processing" title="Natural language processing">natural language processing</a>, <a href="/wiki/Text_analytics" class="mw-redirect" title="Text analytics">text analysis</a>, <a href="/wiki/Computational_linguistics" title="Computational linguistics">computational linguistics</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Biometrics" title="Biometrics">biometrics</a> to systematically identify, extract, quantify, and study affective states and subjective information. Sentiment analysis is widely applied to <a href="/wiki/Voice_of_the_customer" title="Voice of the customer">voice of the customer</a> materials such as reviews and survey responses, online and social media, and healthcare materials for applications that range from <a href="/wiki/Marketing" title="Marketing">marketing</a> to <a href="/wiki/Customer_relationship_management" class="mw-redirect" title="Customer relationship management">customer service</a> to clinical medicine.
</p>
